I created this digital literacy awareness poster using Photoshop and Canva, an online design tool that offers templates, icons, and easy drag-and-drop features. Canva made it simple to organize different sections and maintain a visually appealing layout with consistent colors and fonts.

My design focuses on explaining the concept of digital literacy in a retro-isc and engaging way. It includes three main sections: what digital literacy means, safe internet practices, and useful digital tools. The poster highlights key ideas such as using digital tools effectively, understanding online information, and communicating safely. It also provides practical safety tips like using strong passwords and avoiding suspicious links.

One thing I found challenging was balancing the layout so that the poster did not look overcrowded while still including all the important information. However, it was also interesting to experiment with colors, illustrations, and spacing to make the design both informative and visually attractive.
